</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-59_ pf-text-1">Compressions should be made to a depth of about 1.5 inches at a rate of 100-120 per minute.































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-61_ pf-text-1"><strong>Children (1 year to puberty)</strong> - Use one or two hands (as needed for the size and strength of the rescuer) for chest compressions.































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-63_ pf-text-1">Compressions should be about 2 inches deep, maintaining a rate of 100-120 per minute.
































</li></ul><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-65_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The breaths should be gentle and sufficient to raise the chest, with each cycle comprising 30 compressions for 2 breaths.



















